A vintage-style illustration of an ornate brass mailbox with its door hanging open, revealing a complex mechanical interior of interlocking gears, cogs, and clockwork mechanisms that have rusted and seized up. Scattered around the base of the mailbox are dozens of sealed wax-stamped envelopes piling up unopened. The scene is rendered in warm sepia and copper tones with aged paper texture overlay, evoking 1920s technical diagrams. A large skeleton key lies broken in two pieces on cobblestones beside the mailbox, casting a long shadow. The overall mood conveys sophisticated machinery that has fundamentally failed its purpose, with beautiful complexity rendered useless.
